d in the hematoma at the expected location of the biopsy cavity. (e) Mediolateral mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2021210017/asset/images/large/rg.2021210017.fig19a.jpeg" height="1351" width="1825" aria-labelledby="fig19" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19a</span>. Failed marker deployment. <b>(a)</b> Radiograph after marker deployment shows an hourglass marker in the biopsy cavity. <b>(b)</b> Mediolateral postbiopsy mammogram does not show the biopsy marker (circle). <b>(c, d)</b> Targeted US images obtained when the patient returned 2 days later show a hematoma along the biopsy track, with a ribbon marker (arrow in <b>d</b>) placed in the hematoma at the expected location of the biopsy cavity. <b>(e)</b> Mediolateral mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2021210017&amp;id=fig19">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19b" class="graphic" aria-label="Failed marker deployment. (a) Radiograph after marker deployment shows an hourglass marker in the biopsy cavity. (b) Mediolateral postbiopsy mammogram does not show the biopsy marker (circle). (c, d) Targeted US images obtained when the patient returned 2 days later show a hematoma along the biopsy track, with a ribbon marker (arrow in d) placed in the hematoma at the expected location of the biopsy cavity. (e) Mediolateral mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2021210017/asset/images/large/rg.2021210017.fig19b.jpeg" height="1351" width="1123" aria-labelledby="fig19b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19b</span>. Failed marker deployment. <b>(a)</b> Radi