l mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2021210017&amp;id=fig19c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19d" class="graphic" aria-label="Failed marker deployment. (a) Radiograph after marker deployment shows an hourglass marker in the biopsy cavity. (b) Mediolateral postbiopsy mammogram does not show the biopsy marker (circle). (c, d) Targeted US images obtained when the patient returned 2 days later show a hematoma along the biopsy track, with a ribbon marker (arrow in d) placed in the hematoma at the expected location of the biopsy cavity. (e) Mediolateral mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2021210017/asset/images/large/rg.2021210017.fig19d.jpeg" height="1167" width="1459" aria-labelledby="fig19d" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19d</span>. Failed marker deployment. <b>(a)</b> Radiograph after marker deployment shows an hourglass marker in the biopsy cavity. <b>(b)</b> Mediolateral postbiopsy mammogram does not show the biopsy marker (circle). <b>(c, d)</b> Targeted US images obtained when the patient returned 2 days later show a hematoma along the biopsy track, with a ribbon marker (arrow in <b>d</b>) placed in the hematoma at the expected location of the biopsy cavity. <b>(e)</b> Mediolateral mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2021210017&amp;id=fig19d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19e" class="graphic" aria-label="Failed marker deployment. (a) Radiograph after marker deployment shows an hourglass marker in the biopsy cavity. (b) Mediolateral postbiopsy mammogram does not show the biopsy marker (circle). (c, d) Targeted US images obtained when the patient returned 2 days later show a hematoma along the biopsy track, with a ribbon marker (arrow in d) placed in the hematoma at the expected location of the biopsy cavity. (e) Mediolateral mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2021210017/asset/images/large/rg.2021210017.fig19e.jpeg" height="1351" width="1221" aria-labelledby="fig19e" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19e</span>. Failed marker deployment. <b>(a)</b> Radiograph after marker deployment shows an hourglass marker in the biopsy cavity. <b>(b)</b> Mediolateral postbiopsy mammogram does not show the biopsy marker (circle). <b>(c, d)</b> Targeted US images obtained when the patient returned 2 days later show a hematoma along the biopsy track, with a ribbon marker (arrow in <b>d</b>) placed in the hematoma at the expected location of the biopsy cavity. <b>(e)</b> Mediolateral mammogram after marker placement shows the ribbon marker (circle) at the biopsy site cavity.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2021210017&amp;id=fig19e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Park JM, Franken EA Jr, Garg M, Fajardo LL, Niklason LT. Breast tomosynthesis: present considerations and future applications. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2007;27(suppl 1):S231–S240.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.27si075511">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18180229/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Breast+tomosynthesis%3A+present+considerations+and+future+applications&amp;author=JM+Park&amp;author=EA+Jr+Franken&amp;author=M+Garg&amp;author=LL+Fajardo&amp;author=LT+Niklason&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=S231-S240&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.27si075511&amp;pmid=18180229">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">2.</div><div id="r2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Niklason LT, Christian BT, Niklason LE, et al. Digital tomosynthesis in breast imaging. <em>Radiology</em> 1997;205(2):399–406.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiology.205.2.9356620">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9356620/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Digital+tomosynthesis+in+breast+imaging&amp;author=LT+Niklason&amp;author=BT+Christian&amp;author=LE+Niklason&amp;publication_year=1997&amp;journal=Radiology&amp;pages=399-406&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiology.205.2.9356620&amp;pmid=9356620">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">3.</div><div id="r3" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Conant EF, Beaber EF, Sprague BL, et al. Breast cancer screening using tomosynthesis in combination with digital mammography compared to digital mammography alone: a cohort study within the PROSPR consortium. <em>Breast Cancer Res Treat</em> 2016;156(1):109–116.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10549-016-3695-